;RESIDUES 13 - 22, AND 184 - 194 BELONG TO WEAKLY DEFINED
REGIONS.  RESIDUE SER 125 HAS PHI PSI VALUES OUTSIDE OF THE
EXPECTED RANGE BUT THIS IS REAL BUT THIS IS REAL AND IT IS
TRUE FOR ALL METHYLTRANSFERASES IN THAT POSITION.  THAT
RESIDUE IS PART OF THE LOOP THAT IS FOUND TO BE IMPORTANT
FOR THE CATALYTIC PART OF THE LOOP THAT IS FOUND TO BE
IMPORTANT FOR THE CATALYTIC ACTIVITY AND UNIQUE FOR
METHYLTRANSFERASES.  BACKBONE ANGLES FOR REGION 121 - 127
ARE ALSO DEVIATING BUT THEY TOO ARE INVOLVED IN FORMATION
OF THIS SPECIFIC LOOP.
;
